1
00:00:08,107 --> 00:00:09,587
As if in a dreamland

2
00:00:09,847 --> 00:00:11,400
Magical powers given to me

3
00:00:11,760 --> 00:00:13,527
The bag's treasures

4
00:00:15,900 --> 00:00:17,420
Traveling together in the universe

5
00:00:17,687 --> 00:00:19,346
Capturing above the galaxy

6
00:00:19,460 --> 00:00:21,553
The beauty of time

7
00:00:23,473 --> 00:00:25,220
If problems are encountered

8
00:00:25,440 --> 00:00:30,313
Transforming anytime and anywhere, seemingly full of inspiration

9
00:00:30,726 --> 00:00:33,080
Quickly fly to a delightful and carefree paradise

10
00:00:33,230 --> 00:00:35,030
Holding hands with the starlight

11
00:00:35,055 --> 00:00:37,752
Dancing and shimmering

12
00:00:39,133 --> 00:00:42,693
Casually step through this door

13
00:00:42,967 --> 00:00:46,647
Achieve ideals, dreams come true

14
00:00:47,047 --> 00:00:50,674
Across railways and the countryside

15
00:00:50,847 --> 00:00:54,414
In an instant, the Dream Express reappears

16
00:00:54,774 --> 00:00:55,960
sha la la la la

17
00:00:56,147 --> 00:00:58,567
Accompany me to sing together

18
00:00:58,774 --> 00:01:00,000
Singing Encore loudly

19
00:01:00,100 --> 00:01:02,566
Let's go have fun marching

20
00:01:02,620 --> 00:01:03,847
Doraemon

21
00:01:03,960 --> 00:01:05,893
Let this moment not grow old

22
00:01:05,920 --> 00:01:09,967
Dreams can finally be achieved

23
00:01:10,347 --> 00:01:11,587
sha la la la la

24
00:01:11,767 --> 00:01:14,000
Accompany me to sing together

25
00:01:14,340 --> 00:01:15,540
Singing aloud

26
00:01:15,847 --> 00:01:18,137
Let's go for a stroll together

27
00:01:18,291 --> 00:01:19,524
Doraemon

28
00:01:19,591 --> 00:01:21,531
Let this moment not grow old

29
00:01:21,584 --> 00:01:28,917
Beautiful scenery will be seen

30
00:01:31,338 --> 00:01:34,328
[Moving House with a Relocation Map]

31
00:01:46,094 --> 00:01:48,421
Nobita, you're late again!

32
00:01:50,634 --> 00:01:51,468
That's right...

33
00:01:51,509 --> 00:01:52,960
Nobita, you're outrageous!

34
00:01:53,001 --> 00:01:54,347
You're always late!

35
00:01:54,388 --> 00:01:56,768
Why are you so slow at everything you do?

36
00:01:57,406 --> 00:01:59,905
You just need to leave a little earlier!

37
00:01:59,946 --> 00:02:01,679
I know, but...

38
00:02:01,720 --> 00:02:04,160
I, for one, have never been late!

39
00:02:04,836 --> 00:02:08,562
Because my house is right next to the school

40
00:02:11,573 --> 00:02:13,377
You're so lucky

41
00:02:15,470 --> 00:02:18,025
Mom, I have something to ask you

42
00:02:18,196 --> 00:02:20,129
Something to ask me, what is it?

43
00:02:20,170 --> 00:02:22,701
Can we move next to school?

44
00:02:22,742 --> 00:02:25,207
Living closer to school means I won't be late anymore

45
00:02:25,248 --> 00:02:27,194
Don't say such impossible things!

46
00:02:27,235 --> 00:02:29,134
You just need to wake up earlier!

47
00:02:30,430 --> 00:02:31,877
There are still other ways...

48
00:02:31,917 --> 00:02:34,190
We could just move the school next to our house

49
00:02:35,378 --> 00:02:36,258
Move the school?

50
00:02:36,299 --> 00:02:37,883
Just use this!

51
00:02:39,737 --> 00:02:41,782
"Relocation Map"

52
00:02:42,520 --> 00:02:45,122
First, call out the place you want to move the building to

53
00:02:45,162 --> 00:02:46,535
Our district!

54
00:02:49,860 --> 00:02:51,855
That's the school

55
00:02:51,979 --> 00:02:53,515
This is this house

56
00:02:53,876 --> 00:02:56,765
First, peel off the school sticker

57
00:02:58,877 --> 00:03:01,369
Then peel off the stickers of the houses in front of our house

58
00:03:01,410 --> 00:03:04,280
Swap them and stick them all back down, done!

59
00:03:04,321 --> 00:03:05,701
What happens after that?

60
00:03:05,748 --> 00:03:07,555
Look out the window and see

61
00:03:12,249 --> 00:03:13,544
Like this?

62
00:03:14,210 --> 00:03:16,541
The school is right in front of the house!

63
00:03:17,023 --> 00:03:19,290
It will become the same as the map

64
00:03:21,090 --> 00:03:22,535
Amazing!

65
00:03:24,563 --> 00:03:27,208
This way you won't have to worry about being late anymore

66
00:03:29,163 --> 00:03:31,249
Thank you, Doraemon

67
00:03:36,113 --> 00:03:38,893
So Nobita's house is this close?

68
00:03:40,618 --> 00:03:41,996
Oh, right

69
00:03:42,497 --> 00:03:45,052
I should pay Nobita's house a visit

70
00:03:49,221 --> 00:03:51,681
Well, I just needed to make a surprise visit

71
00:03:51,721 --> 00:03:54,480
to talk about Nobita's score disparity

72
00:03:55,847 --> 00:03:57,895
Please be stricter

73
00:03:57,935 --> 00:04:00,174
Urge Nobita to study harder

74
00:04:00,215 --> 00:04:01,270
Yes

75
00:04:02,537 --> 00:04:03,843
Next time

76
00:04:04,110 --> 00:04:06,760
If you don't get a better score, I won't let you go!

77
00:04:08,293 --> 00:04:09,635
Outrageous

78
00:04:10,679 --> 00:04:11,926
First of all

79
00:04:11,966 --> 00:04:14,332
Go to the bank, then go to the supermarket

80
00:04:14,372 --> 00:04:16,118
What should we have for dinner?

81
00:04:17,813 --> 00:04:21,125
Thinking about it, school so close to home isn't that great

82
00:04:21,166 --> 00:04:22,938
As long as you are willing to study a bit more seriously

83
00:04:22,978 --> 00:04:25,055
then there won't be any problems

84
00:04:25,125 --> 00:04:27,164
Don't say such discouraging things

85
00:04:27,205 --> 00:04:28,181
Nobita

86
00:04:28,554 --> 00:04:30,561
Sorry, this is an urgent letter

87
00:04:30,601 --> 00:04:32,874
Go to the post office and mail it for me right away

88
00:04:33,701 --> 00:04:36,262
By the way, buy me some stamps

89
00:04:37,040 --> 00:04:40,001
To the post office? It's a long way to walk

90
00:04:40,042 --> 00:04:41,710
Okay, we'll move the post office

91
00:04:41,750 --> 00:04:43,803
next to our house!

92
00:04:44,196 --> 00:04:47,475
Okay, swap this one and this one

93
00:04:53,487 --> 00:04:54,780
Here, Dad

94
00:04:57,569 --> 00:04:59,040
So fast?

95
00:04:59,633 --> 00:05:00,534
So clever!

96
00:05:00,575 --> 00:05:02,848
Move some more over here, we can make it even more convenient!

97
00:05:02,889 --> 00:05:03,681
Okay!

98
00:05:04,130 --> 00:05:06,373
Let's turn the back of the house into a park

99
00:05:09,221 --> 00:05:11,958
Let's put Shizuka's house next to ours

100
00:05:13,791 --> 00:05:17,331
Now I can see Shizuka every day with ease!

101
00:05:28,736 --> 00:05:31,709
Becoming neighbors, there will still be such things

102
00:05:32,170 --> 00:05:33,772
In order to be able to play conveniently

103
00:05:33,812 --> 00:05:35,805
Put the vacant lot next to us

104
00:05:35,846 --> 00:05:37,988
Full attack, Gian!

105
00:05:41,350 --> 00:05:43,210
- So sorry!
- So sorry!

106
00:05:52,757 --> 00:05:55,977
Huh? This isn't Mr. Shigemi's house?

107
00:05:56,018 --> 00:05:57,677
It's Nobita's house

108
00:05:58,385 --> 00:06:00,233
Gian, Suneo

109
00:06:01,199 --> 00:06:02,218
Nobita

110
00:06:02,319 --> 00:06:03,826
What are you doing?

111
00:06:07,137 --> 00:06:09,764
You can change this area however you want with this?

112
00:06:09,805 --> 00:06:11,478
It sounds interesting

113
00:06:12,252 --> 00:06:13,765
Let us try it too

114
00:06:14,638 --> 00:06:15,905
Okay!

115
00:06:16,410 --> 00:06:17,580
First…

116
00:06:17,621 --> 00:06:20,528
Move the toy store next to my house

117
00:06:22,253 --> 00:06:25,693
Move the bookstore that sells a lot of comics over here

118
00:06:25,913 --> 00:06:28,487
Move the shop that sells red bean paste buns here

119
00:06:28,580 --> 00:06:29,466
That's right

120
00:06:29,507 --> 00:06:31,767
My home should also move near the open lot

121
00:06:34,758 --> 00:06:36,785
You mean near my home?

122
00:06:37,059 --> 00:06:38,326
If you want to move

123
00:06:38,366 --> 00:06:40,965
How about moving to a more open place

124
00:06:41,344 --> 00:06:42,598
Oh, that's good

125
00:06:44,965 --> 00:06:46,680
No…

126
00:06:46,720 --> 00:06:48,635
Isn't near the school better?

127
00:06:48,729 --> 00:06:50,176
Convenient, right?

128
00:06:50,217 --> 00:06:52,395
Oh, yeah, that sounds good

129
00:06:55,053 --> 00:06:57,886
But there are so many mansions here

130
00:07:01,679 --> 00:07:02,565
Right

131
00:07:02,606 --> 00:07:05,499
Why don’t you move to a place with a better view?

132
00:07:07,313 --> 00:07:08,440
That's good too

133
00:07:08,600 --> 00:07:10,193
Here is good

134
00:07:13,049 --> 00:07:14,216
Are you guys

135
00:07:14,256 --> 00:07:16,197
Really unwilling to be near me?

136
00:07:16,308 --> 00:07:17,923
No, how could that be?

137
00:07:18,470 --> 00:07:20,157
No, no
No, no

138
00:07:21,640 --> 00:07:23,980
Alright, we need to hurry back

139
00:07:28,947 --> 00:07:32,181
Huh? It seems to have changed since just now

140
00:07:36,355 --> 00:07:38,808
There's a house like this here?

141
00:07:40,062 --> 00:07:41,942
Which direction is it?

142
00:07:41,983 --> 00:07:43,680
Uh... let me think...

143
00:07:43,734 --> 00:07:45,841
I remember now, it's that intersection

144
00:07:51,679 --> 00:07:52,792
Change it a bit more!

145
00:07:52,833 --> 00:07:54,233
- Yes!
- Hey, Nobita!

146
00:07:54,433 --> 00:07:55,619
Doraemon!

147
00:07:55,819 --> 00:07:57,193
- Yes!
- Yes!

148
00:07:58,686 --> 00:08:00,158
- How about this one?
- Okay

149
00:08:00,345 --> 00:08:03,757
Mom went out to buy something, but she's taking a long time to come back

150
00:08:03,798 --> 00:08:05,884
Did he say anything?

151
00:08:07,220 --> 00:08:08,403
Could it be...

152
00:08:08,717 --> 00:08:10,878
Mom got lost and can't find her way home?

153
00:08:12,678 --> 00:08:14,830
Quick, we have to go pick up Mom!

154
00:08:14,960 --> 00:08:16,095
Mom!

155
00:08:16,570 --> 00:08:18,450
Where on earth did Nobita go?

156
00:08:18,491 --> 00:08:19,771
Suneo, how about we think of something...

157
00:08:19,811 --> 00:08:22,248
You ought to move something more interesting here.

158
00:08:22,289 --> 00:08:23,711
Oh, is that so...

159
00:08:25,025 --> 00:08:26,905
There's also a piece of paper stuck to the bottom.

160
00:08:26,946 --> 00:08:27,810
Well, then

161
00:08:27,851 --> 00:08:30,304
We can use that paper to display other places

162
00:08:30,363 --> 00:08:32,430
Let's move those over here!

163
00:08:32,471 --> 00:08:35,098
Move all the tourist spots around the world here!

164
00:08:35,411 --> 00:08:37,399
Which attractions should we move first?

165
00:08:37,932 --> 00:08:39,756
Where did Mom go?

166
00:08:39,797 --> 00:08:41,955
It must be the supermarket she usually goes to!

167
00:08:43,248 --> 00:08:45,622
The supermarket is at the corner of the bakery!

168
00:08:45,663 --> 00:08:46,796
No, wait a moment

169
00:08:46,836 --> 00:08:49,543
I remember the bakery and the fish shop were swapped

170
00:08:51,239 --> 00:08:53,194
Where is the fish shop?

171
00:08:53,834 --> 00:08:55,801
I don't know anymore.

172
00:08:56,659 --> 00:08:57,885
Officer!

173
00:08:58,080 --> 00:09:00,300
Excuse me, where is the supermarket?

174
00:09:00,340 --> 00:09:01,206
I'm sorry

175
00:09:01,246 --> 00:09:03,713
I don't even know where the police box is

176
00:09:05,153 --> 00:09:06,470
This won't do

177
00:09:06,511 --> 00:09:07,928
It must be over there!

178
00:09:14,493 --> 00:09:17,741
It must be Gian and Suneo messing with the map again

179
00:09:17,782 --> 00:09:20,468
We need to find Mom quickly now!

180
00:09:33,822 --> 00:09:34,435
Right

181
00:09:34,475 --> 00:09:37,295
Since we're changing it anyway, why not make it an international city?

182
00:09:37,336 --> 00:09:38,335
Okay!

183
00:09:38,954 --> 00:09:42,186
I remember turning left at this laundromat

184
00:09:45,541 --> 00:09:46,495
Huh?

185
00:09:46,535 --> 00:09:49,661
Mr. Yamada's house reconstruction is gorgeous

186
00:09:51,186 --> 00:09:53,129
I remember, after passing through this alley

187
00:09:53,169 --> 00:09:54,782
should be the shopping street

188
00:10:03,237 --> 00:10:05,464
Buongiorno, signora

189
00:10:05,971 --> 00:10:06,751
Buongior...

190
00:10:06,792 --> 00:10:10,140
Signorina, feel free to look and shop

191
00:10:10,366 --> 00:10:12,333
Yes, the weather is great today.

192
00:10:12,680 --> 00:10:14,267
Where is this place?

193
00:10:26,031 --> 00:10:27,948
Even the Statue of Liberty...

194
00:10:27,989 --> 00:10:30,702
At this point, all we can do is go to the sky to find Mom

195
00:10:39,522 --> 00:10:41,881
The mountain behind turned into a pyramid!

196
00:10:52,769 --> 00:10:57,348
Strong and robust, incredibly impressive!

197
00:10:57,389 --> 00:11:01,050
My name is Gian!

198
00:11:01,363 --> 00:11:05,347
With all my heart, I have high tension!

199
00:11:05,736 --> 00:11:09,510
I am a little overlord!

200
00:11:13,979 --> 00:11:18,302
Debut to the whole world!

201
00:11:22,632 --> 00:11:26,405
Gian is here!

202
00:11:28,153 --> 00:11:31,106
Gian and his gang are causing chaos

203
00:11:41,073 --> 00:11:42,933
Mom!

204
00:11:44,670 --> 00:11:46,798
Nobita, Doraemon!

205
00:11:48,570 --> 00:11:51,030
Mom, I miss you so much

206
00:11:55,159 --> 00:11:56,606
This is outrageous!

207
00:11:56,647 --> 00:11:59,339
Restore everything immediately!

208
00:12:00,567 --> 00:12:02,879
- I'm really sorry!
- I'm really sorry!

209
00:12:03,886 --> 00:12:06,709
This belongs here, this belongs here

210
00:12:06,750 --> 00:12:08,832
Is the Eiffel Tower in Egypt?

211
00:12:08,873 --> 00:12:10,312
It's in France

212
00:12:11,278 --> 00:12:13,425
I have no idea what to put where

213
00:12:17,986 --> 00:12:19,271
I'm going to school!

214
00:12:22,073 --> 00:12:24,420
Great, I won't be late today

215
00:12:27,113 --> 00:12:29,206
How could this happen? I have no idea

216
00:12:29,247 --> 00:12:31,152
The school building was rebuilt?

217
00:12:33,080 --> 00:12:36,034
It seems we left the school here

218
00:12:38,494 --> 00:12:40,220
I'm so tired

219
00:12:43,493 --> 00:12:45,993
[Advertising with a Mirror]

220
00:12:47,365 --> 00:12:50,512
Mom, can I have an extra 300 yen for allowance?

221
00:12:50,553 --> 00:12:53,332
No, you need to save your money through to the end of the month

222
00:12:53,373 --> 00:12:55,153
Mom, please help me out

223
00:12:55,194 --> 00:12:57,649
There's a manga I really want to buy

224
00:13:01,218 --> 00:13:06,224
- There's a monster!
- There's a monster!

225
00:13:10,783 --> 00:13:12,776
It's the same monster as before!

226
00:13:12,817 --> 00:13:14,610
What's going on?

227
00:13:15,189 --> 00:13:17,289
I did a little experiment

228
00:13:19,370 --> 00:13:21,596
"Image Projection Mirror"

229
00:13:22,309 --> 00:13:23,790
The image that this mirror reflects

230
00:13:23,830 --> 00:13:26,143
will also be displayed on other mirrors

231
00:13:27,650 --> 00:13:29,928
its projection range can be adjusted at will

232
00:13:29,968 --> 00:13:32,447
from the house to the entire town

233
00:13:32,870 --> 00:13:34,252
Set to automatic mode

234
00:13:34,292 --> 00:13:36,778
It will automatically project when someone looks in the mirror

235
00:13:36,815 --> 00:13:38,739
You really scared me just now!

236
00:13:38,792 --> 00:13:39,870
That's right

237
00:13:39,910 --> 00:13:41,951
I was so scared my heart almost jumped out

238
00:13:41,992 --> 00:13:43,212
So sorry

239
00:13:43,253 --> 00:13:45,731
But what's the use of this gadget of yours?

240
00:13:45,772 --> 00:13:47,298
It's completely useless

241
00:13:47,451 --> 00:13:50,240
At most, it can be used to scare people like just now

242
00:13:50,397 --> 00:13:52,602
Actually, keeping it here is also quite useless

243
00:13:52,969 --> 00:13:54,030
Break it, then

244
00:13:54,070 --> 00:13:54,930
Wait!

245
00:13:55,170 --> 00:13:56,802
That would be a pity

246
00:13:56,843 --> 00:13:58,226
Let's think about it more

247
00:13:58,267 --> 00:14:00,800
Maybe we can think of a good use for it?

248
00:14:00,841 --> 00:14:03,353
What? I don't think it's possible

249
00:14:08,799 --> 00:14:10,625
What use could it possibly have?

250
00:14:12,039 --> 00:14:14,185
I think it should be useful

251
00:14:18,168 --> 00:14:20,582
I still can't think of anything

252
00:14:21,208 --> 00:14:23,161
The latest issue of the "Happy Bug" comic

253
00:14:23,202 --> 00:14:25,028
This month's cover looks like this

254
00:14:26,696 --> 00:14:28,699
That comic I really want to read

255
00:14:31,870 --> 00:14:34,726
I've got it, I've thought of a great use!

256
00:14:34,913 --> 00:14:36,226
It's advertising!

257
00:14:36,337 --> 00:14:38,445
Let's get all the stores's advertisements!

258
00:14:38,485 --> 00:14:41,011
Then we'll broadcast advertisements on all the mirrors in the city!

259
00:14:41,605 --> 00:14:42,830
So that's it!

260
00:14:42,870 --> 00:14:44,727
Nobita, you're so smart!

261
00:14:45,600 --> 00:14:47,300
We can make some money!

262
00:14:48,296 --> 00:14:48,950
Like this

263
00:14:48,990 --> 00:14:51,930
A 15-second ad costs the client 100 yen

264
00:14:51,970 --> 00:14:53,958
There are 60 minutes in an hour

265
00:14:53,999 --> 00:14:55,624
So that means…

266
00:14:57,516 --> 00:15:00,403
Oh dear, it might take a whole hour to calculate how much!

267
00:15:00,444 --> 00:15:01,971
That's 24,000 yen

268
00:15:02,204 --> 00:15:03,370
That much?

269
00:15:03,410 --> 00:15:04,461
If there's that much

270
00:15:04,501 --> 00:15:06,707
The comics I couldn't buy before, I can buy them now!

271
00:15:06,748 --> 00:15:08,950
We can even eat red bean paste buns as much as we want

272
00:15:09,127 --> 00:15:09,744
Alright!

273
00:15:09,785 --> 00:15:12,209
We'll start looking for advertising clients tomorrow!

274
00:15:12,250 --> 00:15:13,470
Okay!

275
00:15:17,710 --> 00:15:20,231
Since we're going to look for advertising clients

276
00:15:24,732 --> 00:15:26,838
We should dress more presentably

277
00:15:26,930 --> 00:15:28,618
- We're leaving!
- We're leaving!

278
00:15:30,832 --> 00:15:31,579
Hello!

279
00:15:31,619 --> 00:15:32,879
Sorry to bother you!

280
00:15:33,988 --> 00:15:35,042
Advertising?

281
00:15:35,083 --> 00:15:37,442
Yes, as long as you use this image projector

282
00:15:37,482 --> 00:15:39,102
you can project it onto nearby mirrors

283
00:15:39,142 --> 00:15:41,315
and advertise the products you want to promote!

284
00:15:41,468 --> 00:15:42,408
Doraemon

285
00:15:42,449 --> 00:15:43,600
Yes, yes

286
00:15:47,654 --> 00:15:49,302
Look, it's like this

287
00:15:53,037 --> 00:15:55,065
But I don't need it

288
00:15:55,185 --> 00:15:57,898
Nobody actually looks in the mirror all the time

289
00:15:58,063 --> 00:15:59,599
Sir, please don't worry

290
00:16:00,690 --> 00:16:01,854
It's not just mirrors

291
00:16:01,895 --> 00:16:03,415
Glass and shiny floors

292
00:16:03,455 --> 00:16:05,641
Anything reflective can project!

293
00:16:08,343 --> 00:16:09,718
It's here too!

294
00:16:09,978 --> 00:16:12,812
But advertising with mirrors feels unrealistic

295
00:16:12,852 --> 00:16:13,872
Let's just forget it!

296
00:16:13,913 --> 00:16:15,431
Don't say that

297
00:16:15,472 --> 00:16:17,704
There will definitely be many customers

298
00:16:17,944 --> 00:16:19,190
Welcome!

299
00:16:19,231 --> 00:16:20,643
We have customers!

300
00:16:20,684 --> 00:16:22,117
Please go

301
00:16:22,158 --> 00:16:23,563
How could this happen?

302
00:16:24,130 --> 00:16:25,689
Using mirrors for promotion?

303
00:16:25,730 --> 00:16:27,763
With such good business, why promote?

304
00:16:27,804 --> 00:16:29,685
We are already very busy

305
00:16:29,726 --> 00:16:31,142
Using mirrors for promotion?

306
00:16:31,183 --> 00:16:32,555
These kinds of sales tactics...

307
00:16:32,595 --> 00:16:33,822
We are not interested

308
00:16:33,863 --> 00:16:35,435
Our shop doesn't need it

309
00:16:35,482 --> 00:16:36,927
We don't need it

310
00:16:37,235 --> 00:16:38,935
-No thank you, please leave quickly
-No thank you

311
00:16:38,976 --> 00:16:40,880
- We don't need it, please go.
- Hey, get outta here...

312
00:16:46,070 --> 00:16:48,933
It seems finding advertising clients is really hard

313
00:16:48,974 --> 00:16:51,282
Using mirrors to advertise, to attract attention

314
00:16:51,322 --> 00:16:53,936
I think this method is clearly good

315
00:16:54,670 --> 00:16:56,713
Complaining is not the solution

316
00:16:56,926 --> 00:16:58,643
First, we advertise using mirrors

317
00:16:58,683 --> 00:17:00,683
We'll promote it ourselves

318
00:17:00,842 --> 00:17:01,922
That's right

319
00:17:01,969 --> 00:17:02,856
In that case

320
00:17:02,896 --> 00:17:04,902
Let's just advertise for one shop

321
00:17:04,943 --> 00:17:06,062
Is that okay?

322
00:17:06,983 --> 00:17:08,878
As long as it goes smoothly, the other shops

323
00:17:08,918 --> 00:17:11,758
will definitely look for us to use mirror advertising!

324
00:17:11,908 --> 00:17:14,728
That's my Nobita, you're especially sharp today!

325
00:17:14,769 --> 00:17:16,988
Only today? Am I not usually sharp?

326
00:17:17,680 --> 00:17:20,760
I think we should find shops that aren't doing so well

327
00:17:21,722 --> 00:17:23,473
All the shops are doing great business

328
00:17:23,514 --> 00:17:24,946
Let's try looking in the side streets

329
00:17:28,614 --> 00:17:30,140
What about that shop?

330
00:17:30,842 --> 00:17:32,069
Sounds good

331
00:17:32,345 --> 00:17:34,159
It's run-down and deserted

332
00:17:34,199 --> 00:17:35,864
It looks like it could close down at any moment.

333
00:17:35,905 --> 00:17:36,798
It's simply a

334
00:17:36,838 --> 00:17:39,485
perfect shop for advertising and promotion!

335
00:17:40,185 --> 00:17:41,414
Excuse me.

336
00:17:41,455 --> 00:17:43,608
Run-down and could close down at any moment...

337
00:17:44,051 --> 00:17:45,524
Are you the owner of the shop?

338
00:17:45,971 --> 00:17:47,131
I'm sorry.

339
00:17:47,172 --> 00:17:49,759
It's okay, it's true

340
00:17:50,824 --> 00:17:53,230
Well, the shop does look run-down on the outside

341
00:17:53,271 --> 00:17:55,318
But it's actually very clean

342
00:17:56,934 --> 00:17:58,314
That's true

343
00:17:58,355 --> 00:17:59,944
It's sparkling

344
00:18:00,180 --> 00:18:02,871
Even the floor is spotless

345
00:18:03,070 --> 00:18:05,250
Come, are you interested in trying some?

346
00:18:06,164 --> 00:18:07,764
Such beautiful wagashi

347
00:18:07,805 --> 00:18:09,578
The colors look very beautiful

348
00:18:09,619 --> 00:18:11,514
Wagashi are not only tasty

349
00:18:11,554 --> 00:18:12,971
They also have beautiful appearances

350
00:18:13,011 --> 00:18:15,857
And a seasonal feel and delicate craftsmanship

351
00:18:15,915 --> 00:18:17,587
Then I'll help myself

352
00:18:18,770 --> 00:18:19,850
Wow, this is delicious!

353
00:18:22,530 --> 00:18:24,144
- Yummy!
- Yummy!

354
00:18:24,185 --> 00:18:27,987
That soft and rich sweetness fills my mouth!

355
00:18:28,041 --> 00:18:29,368
Oh, yeah?

356
00:18:29,490 --> 00:18:32,044
In that case, please try the red bean bun too

357
00:18:33,482 --> 00:18:36,470
Red bean bun, I'll help myself!

358
00:18:38,816 --> 00:18:42,580
The bun is very soft, with delicate red bean paste

359
00:18:42,647 --> 00:18:44,740
This is exquisite!

360
00:18:45,000 --> 00:18:46,530
But even if it tastes so good

361
00:18:46,576 --> 00:18:48,670
why aren't customers coming to eat here?

362
00:18:48,920 --> 00:18:50,574
Ever since the big street outside was rebuilt

363
00:18:50,614 --> 00:18:52,705
into a new shopping street

364
00:18:52,746 --> 00:18:55,379
absolutely no customers have been coming to buy stuff.

365
00:18:55,536 --> 00:18:58,077
Originally, I had thought about renovating the shop

366
00:18:58,118 --> 00:19:00,537
But there are simply no customers coming

367
00:19:01,150 --> 00:19:03,076
It's really quite a headache

368
00:19:04,242 --> 00:19:06,457
Please rest easy, leave it to me!

369
00:19:06,677 --> 00:19:08,492
Let's make advertisements for Araware

370
00:19:08,533 --> 00:19:10,565
And turn this place into the bustling

371
00:19:10,605 --> 00:19:12,292
most popular shop!

372
00:19:12,922 --> 00:19:14,155
Impossible

373
00:19:14,196 --> 00:19:17,081
Also, I don't have the money to film commercials

374
00:19:17,156 --> 00:19:19,082
I won't charge any fees

375
00:19:20,092 --> 00:19:23,126
We hope as many people as possible can know that this shop

376
00:19:23,166 --> 00:19:26,424
Has such delicious red bean buns and wagashi!

377
00:19:26,465 --> 00:19:27,839
Could that really work?

378
00:19:29,230 --> 00:19:30,051
Alright

379
00:19:30,091 --> 00:19:32,764
The broadcast range will be set to the entire city

380
00:19:32,805 --> 00:19:33,378
Well, then

381
00:19:33,418 --> 00:19:36,217
The promotion will use these two types of wagashi, right?

382
00:19:36,258 --> 00:19:37,128
Yes

383
00:19:37,208 --> 00:19:38,759
But you don't even have a camera

384
00:19:38,799 --> 00:19:40,778
How can we film the advertisement?

385
00:19:40,938 --> 00:19:42,395
Leave it to us

386
00:19:42,436 --> 00:19:44,108
Doraemon, are you ready?

387
00:19:44,255 --> 00:19:45,282
Ready

388
00:19:45,628 --> 00:19:47,288
Let's start then!

389
00:19:47,558 --> 00:19:48,965
Counting down five seconds

390
00:19:49,006 --> 00:19:52,746
Four, three, two, one

391
00:19:52,979 --> 00:19:53,979
Start!

392
00:19:54,370 --> 00:19:55,905
What do you think of this one?

393
00:19:56,004 --> 00:19:58,231
With a big mirror attached

394
00:19:58,272 --> 00:20:01,279
Araware's wagashi are the triple crown of wagashi!

395
00:20:01,719 --> 00:20:03,511
Red bean buns are on a big sale!

396
00:20:04,598 --> 00:20:06,972
Red bean buns are only 80 yen!

397
00:20:09,425 --> 00:20:12,564
Araware's red bean buns are usually not available for 80 yen!

398
00:20:12,644 --> 00:20:14,311
Hey, what's going on?

399
00:20:14,670 --> 00:20:17,377
In short, it's very delicious, great value, and number one in Japan!

400
00:20:17,418 --> 00:20:18,904
Nobita, you're so mean!

401
00:20:18,990 --> 00:20:20,864
Araware...

402
00:20:21,030 --> 00:20:24,019
- Araware...
- Araware...

403
00:20:24,060 --> 00:20:26,100
Nobita, those two?

404
00:20:27,721 --> 00:20:30,811
Customers should be coming soon

405
00:20:30,852 --> 00:20:33,145
Why isn't anyone coming?

406
00:20:33,431 --> 00:20:35,351
Let me go see what's going on

407
00:20:36,772 --> 00:20:38,592
There are no customers

408
00:20:38,633 --> 00:20:39,656
Here it is!

409
00:20:40,141 --> 00:20:41,348
It's that kid!

410
00:20:41,455 --> 00:20:42,948
Here they come, customers!

411
00:20:42,989 --> 00:20:44,078
Get him!

412
00:20:47,555 --> 00:20:48,729
How could this happen?

413
00:20:48,769 --> 00:20:50,528
Why is everyone so angry?

414
00:20:50,981 --> 00:20:52,974
Nobita, hurry over here!

415
00:20:53,087 --> 00:20:55,006
- Doraemon!
- Don't run...

416
00:20:58,806 --> 00:20:59,853
Strange

417
00:21:00,120 --> 00:21:02,273
Ads like that are a total nuisance!

418
00:21:03,226 --> 00:21:04,287
That scared me

419
00:21:04,328 --> 00:21:05,727
Hurry back

420
00:21:06,322 --> 00:21:08,169
Huh, everyone's angry?

421
00:21:08,210 --> 00:21:09,189
Yes

422
00:21:09,230 --> 00:21:12,217
That's why I didn't really want to advertise in the first place

423
00:21:12,257 --> 00:21:13,803
It's really asking for trouble

424
00:21:13,844 --> 00:21:15,230
- I'm sorry
- I'm sorry

425
00:21:15,271 --> 00:21:18,017
Now customers will be even less likely to come

426
00:21:19,260 --> 00:21:21,097
What should we do now?

427
00:21:21,420 --> 00:21:23,336
If customers don't come and buy stuff

428
00:21:23,615 --> 00:21:26,144
this shop will close down very soon!

429
00:21:27,466 --> 00:21:29,190
It's our fault!

430
00:21:31,662 --> 00:21:32,641
- I'm sorry...
- I'm sorry...

431
00:21:32,682 --> 00:21:34,889
The one who should be crying is me

432
00:21:37,720 --> 00:21:39,119
Forget it, it doesn't matter

433
00:21:39,160 --> 00:21:40,659
Please don't cry anymore

434
00:21:41,260 --> 00:21:43,415
Actually, this month is when I originally planned

435
00:21:43,456 --> 00:21:44,999
to close the shop

436
00:21:45,879 --> 00:21:47,646
Mr. Araware

437
00:21:48,032 --> 00:21:49,211
If you don't mind

438
00:21:49,251 --> 00:21:52,265
Please eat as much as you want of the pastries in the shop

439
00:21:52,497 --> 00:21:54,160
How can we accept this?

440
00:21:54,200 --> 00:21:56,063
We clearly couldn't help you at all

441
00:21:56,107 --> 00:21:57,676
And you still treat us to a meal?

442
00:21:57,827 --> 00:22:00,465
Even though it was only for a moment, I was very happy

443
00:22:00,505 --> 00:22:02,178
Thank you all very much

444
00:22:02,364 --> 00:22:04,762
And also, the way you ate with such enjoyment

445
00:22:04,802 --> 00:22:06,562
I really want to see it once more

446
00:22:06,856 --> 00:22:07,976
- Yes
- Yes

447
00:22:09,373 --> 00:22:11,183
Help yourselves

448
00:22:20,255 --> 00:22:22,117
- Bon appetit!
- Bon appetit!

449
00:22:23,382 --> 00:22:24,757
It's so tasty!

450
00:22:26,063 --> 00:22:27,783
So tasty, I can't stop eating!

451
00:22:28,451 --> 00:22:29,591
Another skewer!

452
00:22:29,632 --> 00:22:31,118
No fair, I want one too!

453
00:22:32,086 --> 00:22:34,473
- Yum!
- Yum!

454
00:22:36,383 --> 00:22:38,018
Looks delicious

455
00:22:38,765 --> 00:22:39,739
Over there

456
00:22:40,078 --> 00:22:42,999
This pomelo cake is really tasty!

457
00:22:43,455 --> 00:22:44,795
It’s the one from earlier

458
00:22:45,055 --> 00:22:47,177
Kintsuba is also the best in the world!

459
00:22:47,723 --> 00:22:50,011
- Mom, buy that one for me
- I can't believe how tasty it is

460
00:22:50,330 --> 00:22:52,070
So happy!

461
00:22:52,111 --> 00:22:54,141
That place is... Araware?

462
00:22:54,487 --> 00:22:56,720
I can't take it anymore, I need to go out for a bit.

463
00:22:57,508 --> 00:22:58,642
I'm going too.

464
00:22:59,177 --> 00:23:00,957
Hey, where are you guys going?

465
00:23:02,568 --> 00:23:04,078
I'm so full

466
00:23:04,269 --> 00:23:06,445
I'm already so full

467
00:23:06,570 --> 00:23:09,041
You're full? There's still a lot left.

468
00:23:09,082 --> 00:23:10,907
Excuse me, I'd like to buy kintsuba.

469
00:23:12,077 --> 00:23:14,017
I want red bean buns and kintsuba.

470
00:23:19,796 --> 00:23:20,891
Welcome!

471
00:23:20,932 --> 00:23:22,111
Yes, coming right up!

472
00:23:23,679 --> 00:23:25,366
Why are there suddenly so many people?

473
00:23:26,610 --> 00:23:27,625
It's this!

474
00:23:27,666 --> 00:23:30,598
The image projection mirror has been on the whole time, filming us

475
00:23:30,769 --> 00:23:31,585
Is that so?

476
00:23:36,120 --> 00:23:38,386
Please, everyone, do not push!

477
00:23:38,520 --> 00:23:40,720
- Thank you... Welcome, everyone!
- Here are your red bean buns.

478
00:23:40,761 --> 00:23:42,826
This is too great, Mr. Araware.

479
00:23:43,013 --> 00:23:44,933
Yes, it's all thanks to you two!

480
00:23:44,974 --> 00:23:46,100
Thank you!

481
00:23:46,141 --> 00:23:48,106
Okay, these are yours

482
00:23:53,028 --> 00:23:54,555
Sha la la la la

483
00:23:54,615 --> 00:23:57,054
Accompany me to sing together

484
00:23:57,141 --> 00:23:58,494
Singing loudly

485
00:23:58,548 --> 00:24:00,982
Let's go have fun and step together

486
00:24:01,161 --> 00:24:02,374
Doraemon

487
00:24:02,429 --> 00:24:04,408
Let this moment not get old

488
00:24:04,441 --> 00:24:10,818
Beautiful scenery can be seen

